==Cricket==
Aside from football, Bell was also an accomplished amateur cricketer; he assisted [[Burnley Cricket Club]] between 1899 and 1919,<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.cricketarchive.com/Archive/Players/252/252979/252979.html|title=AA Bell|publisher=[[CricketArchive]]|accessdate=1 January 2012}}</ref> and would often choose to play cricket rather than football when the seasons overlapped. He was a member of the side that won the [[Lancashire League (cricket)|Lancashire League]] in 1901 and went on to captain the team that won three consecutive titles in 1906, 1907 and 1908. Bell won a fifth Lancashire League title with Burnley in the 1913 season.<ref name="obit"/> A left-handed batsman who often batted in the [[middle order]], he also bowled [[slow left arm]]. Bell represented the [[Lancashire County Cricket Club|Lancashire Second XI]] on three occasions in 1905 and 1906. He was selected for two matches against the [[Surrey County Cricket Club|Surrey]] and [[Yorkshire County Cricket Club|Yorkshire]] second teams during the 1905 season and on 9 July 1906 he played in the [[Minor Counties Championship]] draw with [[Staffordshire County Cricket Club|Staffordshire]] at Turf Moor.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://cricketarchive.com/Archive/Players/63/63339/63339.html|title=Arthur Bell|publisher=CricketArchive|accessdate=1 January 2012}}</ref>

